content:
That's great to hear! It's wonderful that you're enjoying the music meetup group and getting inspiration from the other members. Playing with others can be a fantastic way to improve your skills, learn new things, and stay motivated.

It's also excellent that you're experiencing a mix of covers and originals. Covers can be a great way to learn new songs and techniques, while originals can help you develop your own style and creativity. The diversity of styles and talents in a group setting can be really enriching and help you grow as a musician.

Remember to keep an open mind, be respectful of others' contributions, and don't be afraid to try new things. Music is a collaborative process, and the more you put into it, the more you'll get out of it.

Also, don't hesitate to share your own original songs or ideas with the group. It can be intimidating at first, but it's a great way to get feedback, improve your songwriting, and connect with others who share your passion for music.

Keep rocking, and I hope you continue to have a blast at your music meetup group!
